and I didn't care for him.

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:50.000
And I was on my own more and more.

00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:53.000
And then I remember I was lying in bed,

00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:56.000
and I was talking with my father.

00:12:56.000 --> 00:12:59.000
We had a real one apartment.

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:01.000
And so, what are you going to do, Steve?

00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:04.000
He said, you're 18 years old.

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:08.000
What are you going to do after you graduate from Stuyvesant?

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:10.000
And I don't know where it came from,

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:16.000
but I was trying to become a champion tennis player.

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:20.000
I got the idea that I would leave home,

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:25.000
go to Los Angeles, play tennis and work for you

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:28.000
in the Golden UCLA.

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:33.000
And I laid it out for me, said, that's it.

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:35.000
That's perfect.

00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:37.000
And that's what I did.

00:13:37.000 --> 00:13:41.000
And I got into a car with somebody else

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:46.000
who was driving to Denver, drove to Denver.

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:54.000
Soon LA arrived and LAX, and I didn't know anybody.

00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:57.000
Had some money, then my father gave me,

00:13:57.000 --> 00:14:02.000
ran in a room at the YMCA, and started to work,

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:05.000
and support myself,

00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:10.000
and started my long soldier in that UCLA.

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:13.000
What I spent about twice is what's time,

00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:16.000
and I really needed it.

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:21.000
And what point did you go back to your mother again?

00:14:21.000 --> 00:14:25.000
Did they discover what was going on with your mother?

00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:29.000
Well, after seven or eight years,

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:32.000
her tumor became so bad that she couldn't walk

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:35.000
